{"id":"bestiary-o5v1","title":"MINOR: TestModelConstants_NamingStable docstring overpromises — claims it checks constant NAMES but only checks VALUES","description":"---
references:
  slice: bestiary-ktj
  reviewer: reviewer-C
  round: 1
  leaf_of: bestiary-f3ni
---
## Finding

constants_test.go:TestModelConstants_NamingStable has this docstring:
  // TestModelConstants_NamingStable verifies that Model_* constant names follow
  // the required naming convention:
  //   - Every constant starts with "Model_"
  //   - Underscores are the only separator (no hyphens, no spaces)
  //   - Constant names are non-empty

But Go does not provide runtime reflection over constant names. The test actually verifies:
  (a) ModelIDs() returns non-empty values (no empty string in slice)
  (b) Values do NOT start with "Model_" (would indicate a codegen bug)
  (c) Mutation of the slice does not affect the next call (defensive copy)

The first bullet point of the docstring ('Every constant starts with Model_') is not tested at runtime — this is enforced at compile time (the generated source is checked in). The remaining points in the docstring correspond to what the test checks at the value level, but the framing misleads a reader into thinking constant identifiers are being inspected.

## Why MINOR

Tests pass and the logic is correct. The mismatch is documentation-only: a reader following TDD will expect the test to exercise name-level checking, find it does not, and waste time understanding why.

## How to fix

Update the docstring to describe what is actually verified:
  // TestModelConstants_NamingStable verifies runtime properties of ModelIDs():
  //   - Returns a non-empty slice (>= 1000 constants)
  //   - No empty ModelID values
  //   - Returned values are raw API model IDs (do not start with 'Model_')
  //   - Defensive copy: mutation of one call's result does not affect subsequent calls
  //
  // Note: constant NAME correctness (Model_<Provider>_... naming pattern) is a
  // compile-time guarantee enforced by the generated source in models_constants_gen.go.","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","owner":"dayvidpham@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-04-25T11:14:55Z","created_by":"David Huu Pham","updated_at":"2026-04-25T11:14:55Z"}

